content: Dont save data.

Nice game, and in most cases keeps to the original PC game. One thing developers definitely need to add is a restart map button. Going back to the main menu and back into campaing then into the map isbt an efficient way to restart. This is especially so if you are playing on blood thirsty and are at the whims any opening combat RNG.

The desktop version of Majesty is my favorite game of all time, and unlike many conversions, this captures the feel beautifully. There are perhaps a few places where the storytelling is a bit off (like the developers couldn't just go with the theme and had to insert modern politics in a fantasy game.) Regardless, this is one of the few games that I've tried that merits a permanent place on my phone.

In many aspects I prefer over it's PC predecessor, namely UI and graphics,which are way more fitting aesthetically and I find them to be more clear. It's missing a few classes and buildings though, or at least I haven't found them yet since I'm slowly chugging through the campaign. And wizards are even weaker than in the original.
it's a cool game. however, i'd like to have a possibility to save my progress to the cloud storage. also, it would be nice if i could enlarge the map.

Awesome mobile port, with an exception or two. A few additions it could really benefit from are a zoom in feature, voices that characters had from the original, renaming characters! and the missing buildings from the pc version. Other than that, it's stellar. It just needs the few missing details.
Thank you for fixing the save issue. This game is one of my favorites. Been playing for 4 years
You guys did an awesome job with this game! it reminds me of majesty 2 which was a great game too. one thing I would love to see is a cloud save feature. other than that, great game!

My outgoing data jumped from under 1gb per month to over 13gb in May.  Even monitoring didn't do anything as whatever it was was using playservices. I couldn't work it out. Ran an anti malware app and it flagged this app. Since deleting it my data has dropped back to normal.
Love this game, very faithful to the Pc classic

In a game where I have to issue every order directly, that sort of attitude gets me killed.  Majesty has a beautiful concept. I lay the foundations for a kingdom, and the kingdom runs itself with some prompting from me. This is what I've really wanted, but didn't get, from traditional RTS games.  Highly satisfying.  I regret that the DRM won't allow me to play it offline; network coverage is spotty where I live. Were it not for that detail, this would easily be 5 stars.
